The paper discusses the application of deep learning methods in climate science, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The specific application is in computer vision for climate data, which could also be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses uncertainty quantification, which could fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY) or statistics (cs.ST).
